  "body": "I initially configured a test zone like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\n. {\r\n        proxy . 8.8.8.8\r\n        cache\r\n        chaos CoreDNS-1.0.5 cricket@infoblox.com\r\n        log\r\n        errors\r\n\r\n        file db.foo.example foo.example {\r\n                transfer to *\r\n        }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat worked fine.  But then I moved db.foo.example into /etc/coredns, added a new RR to the zone, added the statement \"root /etc/coredns\" to Corefile, and then sent SIGUSR1 to coredns.  coredns read the modified zone data file (yay!) but continues to look in the old location, according to coredns's error output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2018/02/08 18:30:45 [INFO] Reloading\r\n2018/02/08 18:30:45 [INFO] Reloading complete\r\n2018/02/08 18:30:56 [INFO] Successfully reloaded zone \"foo.example.\" in \"/etc/coredns/db.foo.example\" with serial 2018020801\r\n127.0.0.1 - [08/Feb/2018:18:30:56 +0000] 35360 \"A IN www.foo.example. udp 57 false 4096\" NOERROR qr,aa,rd,ra 93 224.587\u00b5s\r\n2018/02/08 18:31:14 [INFO] Successfully reloaded zone \"foo.example.\" in \"/etc/coredns/db.foo.example\" with serial 2018020801\r\n2018/02/08 18:31:26 [ERROR] Failed to open zone \"foo.example.\" in \"db.foo.example\": open db.foo.example: no such file or directory\r\n2018/02/08 18:31:45 [ERROR] Failed to open zone \"foo.example.\" in \"db.foo.example\": open db.foo.example: no such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\n(Note the two errors at the end.)\r\n\r\nPerhaps coredns isn't deleting the old configuration for the zone?",
